Pescadero Creek Rd.-- Butano Creek riparian area
photos.Observation Details: Continuing bird. Very active - watched for 15 minutes - fed in 8 trees - the red breasted sapsucker in my yard has only used 7 trees in 4 years of watching. Derek got pictures.   Where we found it - along East side of creek about .2 miles north of road - look back towards road and we saw the bird at the last spot you can still see the bridge over the creek.  Separate Red patches at throat, crown and nape - with two lines of white bars along back.  It’s been a while since I have seen a red-naked that is not an intergrade with a red-breasted....
